GAME SIMULATION ENGINE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- Stats-first scoring: TDs/FGs generated from team ratings; player stats
  derived to always match the scoreboard
- Morale modifier: effective OVR = rating × (1 + (morale − 75) × 0.001)
- Coaching modifier (applied in getTeamRatings):
  OC offense_rating: offenseRating += (oc_rating − 70) × 0.15
  DC defense_rating: defenseRating += (dc_rating − 70) × 0.15
  HC overall_rating: both sides += (hc_rating − 70) × 0.05
  A 90-rated OC = +3.0 to offense; a 55-rated DC = −2.25 to defense
- Game script: trailing teams pass more; leading teams run more; desperation
  INTs increase when down 14+
- Overtime: TD wins outright; FG gives opponent a chance; no ties
- Weather: clear / rain / snow / wind with pass, rush, score multipliers
- Home field advantage: +0.5 scoring drives home; away QB accuracy penalty
- Depth chart integration: healthy players by position group; cascades
  to backups; targets distributed proportionally

COACHING STAFF SYSTEM
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- coaching_staff table: id, team_id (NULL = available), role (HC/OC/DC/ST),
  first_name, last_name, overall_rating, offense_rating, defense_rating,
  development_rating, experience, salary, years_remaining
- CoachingRepository: getByTeam, getAvailable, getById, getByTeamAndRole,
  create, assignToTeam, release, countAvailable
- CoachingService:
  - generateAllCoachingStaff(): seeds 32 teams × 4 roles + 16-coach pool
    at first launch; tiered rating generation (Elite 10% / Good 25% /
    Average 35% / Below-Average 30%); role-specific primary/secondary
    rating distribution; salary scaled to primary rating
  - hireCoach(): releases existing role holder, assigns new coach
  - fireCoach(): returns coach to available pool
  - replenishCoachPool(): ensures minimum 3 coaches per role in pool
- IPC handlers: get-coaching-staff, get-available-coaches, hire-coach,
  fire-coach (registered in coachingHandlers.ts)

CONTRACT NEGOTIATION DEPTH
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- dead_cap_entries table: id, team_id, player_id, player_name, position,
  season, amount — written when a player with guaranteed money is released
- ContractRepository:
  - addDeadCap(): inserts a dead cap entry on mid-contract release
  - getDeadCap() / getDeadCapEntries(): season-scoped queries
  - getCapUsage(): sums active contract salaries + dead cap charges
- ContractService:
  - resignPlayer(): returns counterOffer { salary, years } when elite player
    rejects an offer; conditions: OVR 80+, player morale < 65 or offer
    below asking price, random acceptance threshold by OVR tier
  - releasePlayer(): calculates remaining guaranteed amount and writes dead
    cap entry before clearing the contract
  - acceptCounterOffer(): processes accepted counter as a new contract
- IPC handlers: accept-counter-offer, get-dead-cap

